Ask HN: Where is that noise coming from?
text:
As a fun experiment, say you’re in a (mostly) silent house and there is a faint, irregularly timed noise that sounds pretty similar each time.

At your disposal you have yourself, your cat, another person, and two modern smartphones. You’ve tried wandering around, and you just can’t figure it out off the top of your head.

What technical/non-technical method would you use to locate the source of the sound?

title: Confluence on-premise is dead, what now?
text:
Atlassian has killed off their on-premise Confluence product for small to medium sized organisations.

We currently have a 25 user license and would probably upgrade to 50 users in the next year or two. Our only option at the moment is to pay a fortune and a half and upgrade to their 500+ user (on-prem) Datacenter product. By law we are not allowed to use a cloud solution.

Most likely we will have to move to Sharepoint :(

Anyone in a similar situation?

Suggestions and recommendations would be very welcome!
